The ΔG of each elementary step was obtained by minus the Gibbs free energy of reactant with that of product. The Gibbs free energy of (Na+ + e–) was treated with the standard electrode potential of Na+/Na (–2.714 V vs. RHE)55 referred to the computational standard hydrogen electrode approximation51. The driving force of photo-induced hole on TiO2-Ov is determined to be 2.6 eV according to its band edge placement of valence band maximum (2.6 V vs. NHE, Supplementary Fig. 7d). The influence of bias was treated with the computational standard electrode potential approximationC6 with the term “–eU”. The Gibbs free energy of reactant, intermediates, and product were obtained by calculating their phonon density of states, as depicted in Eq. 1:1G=E+ZPE+kT∫F(ω)ln1−exp−ℏωkTdω\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
